column5: Just went that way Saturday, there were no problems.I see Duluth is under another flood watch, I'd check before you leave.Here's a great site with up-to-date info: http://www.511mn.org/
Leaving friday any updates would be appreciated. Thanks, Mike kansas

We just returned from Ear Falls Saturday. On the 53 there were a few small construction projects, but nothing major, delays were maybe in the 5-10 min range. Both crossongs were in near record times!! No new or odd questions like where do you work or if you own any firearms. Have a great trip!!

Road conditions from Duluth to Int'l Falls on Hwy 53 are good. Flood did not cause any permanent problems on this route. Safe travels and have a great trip! 1 month to go and counting down the days to our trip to Lac Seul! RBF!
Sweet!! Mike,I'll be leaving Friday also,let's race.

[QUOTE=fishinnut 3446;1453933]Sweet!! Mike,I'll be leaving Friday also,let's race.[/QUOTE The race is on. I will be the van with the Dallas Cowboy Cheerleaders in it. Hope I remember to pack some fishing gear. Mike Kansas
Lucky guy,I be in a black Tundra pulling a black/silver 185 tpro,maybe at the border we can swap vehicles and you can deal with my wife/kids,and I can play motorboat with the cheerleaders.
See you both on the way up, coming from IL - white pro v 2025 pulled by a F250 crew cab - dark stone metalic.
Does anyone know if the route from Cloquet to Int. Falls is open? I think I read or heard there was a bridge washed out on Hwy. 33? We will be heading that way in 3 weeks.

Hwy 33 North of Cloquet is OPEN and fine for travel to HWY 53 North to Int'l Falls. The bridge that was washed out was on HWY 210 near Carlton MN and another one on Hwy 61 North between Duluth & Two Harbors. Small detour there.
Leaving Cent. Wisconsin on fri morning, heading to Wabbie. Seems to be getting crowded up there. Red Ford Edge pulling a Smoker.........
